extends base

block content
  main.main
    .career-hero
      .career-hero__overlay
      h1.heading-primary
        span Privacy Policy
    
    section.section-privacy
      .container
        p.privacy-intro Last updated: January 2025
        
        .privacy-content
          h2.heading-secondary Introduction
          p
            | At Vistara, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website and use our services.
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Information We Collect
          
          h3.heading-tertiary Personal Information
          p We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us when you:
          ul.privacy-list
            li Register for an account on our website
            li Book a tour or make a reservation
            li Subscribe to our newsletter
            li Contact us through our contact form or email
            li Participate in surveys or promotions
          
          p This information may include:
          ul.privacy-list
            li Name and contact information (email address, phone number, mailing address)
            li Date of birth and nationality
            li Payment information (processed securely through our payment providers)
            li Passport details (when required for tour bookings)
            li Dietary restrictions and health information (when relevant for tour planning)
            li Profile photo and user preferences
          
          h3.heading-tertiary.ma-top-md Automatically Collected Information
          p When you visit our website, we automatically collect certain information about your device and browsing behavior:
          ul.privacy-list
            li IP address and browser type
            li Operating system and device information
            li Pages visited and time spent on pages
            li Referring website addresses
            li Click patterns and navigation paths
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg How We Use Your Information
          
          p We use the information we collect for various purposes:
          ul.privacy-list
            li To process your tour bookings and reservations
            li To communicate with you about your bookings, including confirmations and updates
            li To provide customer support and respond to your inquiries
            li To send you marketing communications (with your consent)
            li To improve our website, services, and user experience
            li To detect, prevent, and address technical issues or fraudulent activities
            li To comply with legal obligations and enforce our terms and conditions
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Cookies and Tracking Technologies
          
          p We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:
          ul.privacy-list
            li Remember your preferences and settings
            li Keep you logged in to your account
            li Analyze website traffic and user behavior
            li Provide personalized content and recommendations
            li Deliver targeted advertising
          
          p You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences. However, disabling cookies may limit your ability to use certain features of our website.
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Data Sharing and Disclosure
          
          p We do not sell your personal information to third parties. We may share your information with:
          ul.privacy-list
            li Tour operators and service providers necessary to fulfill your bookings
            li Payment processors to handle transactions securely
            li Analytics and marketing service providers
            li Legal authorities when required by law or to protect our rights
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Data Security
          
          p We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. These measures include:
          ul.privacy-list
            li Encryption of sensitive data during transmission (SSL/TLS)
            li Secure servers and databases with access controls
            li Regular security assessments and updates
            li Employee training on data protection practices
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Your Rights
          
          p You have the right to:
          ul.privacy-list
            li Access the personal information we hold about you
            li Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information
            li Request deletion of your personal information (subject to legal obligations)
            li Object to or restrict certain processing of your information
            li Withdraw consent for marketing communications at any time
            li Request a copy of your data in a portable format
          
          p To exercise these rights, please contact us at privacy@vistara.com
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Data Retention
          
          p We retain your personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. Booking and transaction records are typically retained for 7 years for accounting and legal purposes.
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Children's Privacy
          
          p Our services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe we have collected information from a child, please contact us immediately.
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg International Data Transfers
          
          p Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Changes to This Privacy Policy
          
          p We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated policy on our website and updating the "Last updated" date.
          
          h2.heading-secondary.ma-top-lg Contact Us
          
          p If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
          p
